ExecDesc.value: Digium Asterisk SIP sscanf Multiple Denial of Service Vulnerabilities

EngDesc.value: A denial of service vulnerability has been reported in Asterisk SIP Channel Driver. The vulnerability is due to insufficient input validation when processing maliciously crafted SIP requests. Remote authenticated attackers could exploit this vulnerability by crafting SIP requests that contain excessively long numeric strings. Successful exploitation could result in a denial of service condition.
